The White House announced that President Sarkozy of France will visit the White House on March 30th. They will discuss various strategic issues including Afghanistan, Iran, and Middle East peace efforts. The President also announced his support for repealing the antitrust exemption currently enjoyed by health insurers, as part of the effort to promote competition and reduce healthcare costs. Press Secretary Robert Gibbs addressed concerns about the President's plan for comprehensive healthcare reform, stating that the President is focused on Thursday's summit and hopes for a productive discussion among Democrats and Republicans. He also addressed questions about the Volcker rule and Wall Street bonuses, expressing the administration's commitment to the original proposal and its frustration with compensation practices on Wall Street. Gibbs stated that the President will outline a vision for a more competitive America during a dinner with business leaders, and he will discuss this vision in a speech the following day.